{"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Class","title":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"c:@M@OUDSTokensSemantic@objc(cs)MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","modules":[{"name":"Tokens for semantics"}],"symbolKind":"class"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["        \/\/ Assuming in Figma with have a font semantic token displayLarge,","        \/\/ with values depending to size class. These values are defined as font composite raw tokens.","        let bold850 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: size850, lineHeight: lineHeight1050, weight: weight700, letterSpacing: letterSpacing850)","        let bold1450 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: size1450, lineHeight: lineHeight1850, weight: weight700, letterSpacing: letterSpacing1450)","","        \/\/ Then the develoment team declares an \"higher\" level font semantic token","        \/\/ inside FontCompositeSemanticTokens protocol,","        \/\/ and defined inside OUDSTheme+FontCompositeSemanticTokens extension","        var displayLarge: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens {","            MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(compact: FontRawTokens.bold850, regular: FontRawTokens.bold1450)","        }","","        \/\/ If the same font is used whatever the size class is","        var displayLarge: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens { MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(FontRawTokens.bold650) }","","        \/\/ The theme exposes both generated elevation semantic tokens and \"crafted\" higher level elevation semantic tokens.","        \/\/ It is recommended to use the higher level version as it is less error-prone."]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The case of this ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is quite particular because in fact it contains ","type":"text"},{"code":"FontCompositeRawToken","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(i.e. raw tokens) instead of semantic tokens.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In fact there is not “font composite semantic tokens” defined in the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" kit.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Since","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.8.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(cs)NSObject"],"type":"inheritsFrom"},{"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(pl)NSObject","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s7CVarArgP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s28CustomDebugStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SQ","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SH","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Kind of semantic tokens which will wrap a